caption:
Henry, a Nile crocodile born in 1900 in Botswana, is the world’s oldest known crocodile at 124 years old. 

Captured in 1903 for preying on locals, he now lives at Crocworld Conservation Centre in South Africa. Measuring nearly 16 feet and weighing around 1,540 pounds, Henry has fathered over 10,000 offspring since 1985 and remains active despite his age.
